Our God, our ancientsÚ God:/PR
May it be your will that a heavenly inspiration/PR
be awakened in us on this holy day/PR
to rebuild the Land of Israel,/PR
to renew it and to make it holy for your service,/PR
and may peace prevail there,/PR
as well as freedom, justice, and the rule of Law,/PR
as it is written by your prophet:/PR
"Truly, Torah shall go forth from Zion,/PR
and the word of /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL/XX from Jerusalem!"/PR
And it is said: "Let none do harm,/PR
let none destroy, throughout my holy mountain,/PR
for the earth is filled with knowledge of the /SCO/XXMNIPRESENT/XX,/PR
as the waters fill the sea."/PR
And place over us, /SCE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God,/PR
the blessing of your Festivals,/PR
for life, for peace, for happiness, and for rejoicing,/PR
as you have desired and promised to bless us./PR
(Our God, our ancientsÚ God,/PR
take pleasure in our rest.)/PR
Enable us to realize holiness through your mitzvot,/PR
give us our portion in your Torah,/PR
let us enjoy the good things of your world,/PR
and gladden us with your salvation./PR
Refine our hearts to serve you honestly,/PR
and help us to perpetuate, /SCD/XXEAR /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God,/PR
(with love and with desire,) with happiness and joy,/PR
(the Shabbat and)/PR
your holy Festivals,/PR
and let all Israel, and all who treat your name as holy,/PR
rejoice in you. Blessed are you, /SCE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX,/PR
source of the holiness of/PR
(the Shabbat, and of)/PR
Israel and the Festivals./PI/PR
